<HEADLINE> Dow Falls 22; Nasdaq Up a Point  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- The Dow Jones industrial average is down 22
points in today's early going. Advancing and declining issues on
the New York Stock Exchange are evenly split.
</P>
<P>
   The Nasdaq Composite Index is ahead a point and the Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500 Stock Index is down two points.
</P>
<P>
   Earnings news is expected to be the driver behind much of
today's stock action.
</P>
<P>
   Wall Street will get the chance to react to a host of earnings
this morning and since the closing bell yesterday.
</P>
<P>
   Shares of eBay and Compaq are among those that have moved higher
in premarket activity.
</P>
<P>
   After the closing bell today, Amazon.com is expected to release
its quarterly figures.
</P>
<P>
   Bond prices are modestly higher after a report showing the first
increase in durable goods orders this year.
</P>
