<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-26 12:41 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Five Questions With Peter Facinelli  </HEADLINE>
By ELIZABETH A. KENNEDY, Associated Press Writer
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Growing up in Queens, N.Y., Peter Facinelli
wanted to be a lawyer until he realized one thing: ''I think I have
an allergic reaction to suits.''
</P>
<P>
   This problem did not interfere with his impressive performance
as a young, straight-laced industrial lubricant salesman in the new
movie ''The Big Kahuna,'' which also stars Kevin Spacey and Danny
DeVito.
</P>
<P>
   Facinelli plays Bob. He and co-workers Larry (Spacey) and Phil
(DeVito) await the arrival of an important potential client at a
trade convention. Over the course of one night, the three salesmen
open up to each other and reveal some powerful conflicts.
</P>
<P>
   His previous film roles include ''Can't Hardly Wait'' and
''Dancer, Texas Pop. 81.'' But ''The Big Kahuna'' stands out for
the 26-year-old actor, who describes the screenplay as ''very
complex'' and ''some of the best writing I had ever read.''
</P>
<P>
   Facinelli lives in Los Angeles with his girlfriend Jennie Garth
(''Beverly Hills, 90210'') and their 2-year-old daughter Luca
Bella.
</P>
<P>
   But he enjoys coming back to New York to visit his family and to
savor the city's ''wonderful creative atmosphere.''
</P>
<P>
   ''I remember when I was studying acting at New York University.
When I came out of class into Washington Square Park, there were
all these students writing poetry and painting. I like that
mosh-posh of different cultures and people,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   After a night of karaoke in downtown Manhattan -- where he sang
Elvis Presley's ''Hound Dog'' -- Facinelli sat down to talk about
his new film.
</P>
<P>
   1. The character you play in ''The Big Kahuna'' is a strict
Christian who thinks it is important that others know what he
believes. Do you think it's important that people know your
beliefs?
</P>
<P>
   Facinelli: No, I don't. For me, I have a set of beliefs and my
rules that I live by. I try not to come from a judgmental place, so
I don't try to instill them on other people. Everyone has to do
their own thing. Everybody strives for goodness. I wouldn't want to
tell people how to get there.
</P>
<P>
   2. Your co-stars are established Hollywood actors. Did you feel
intimidated working with Kevin Spacey and Danny DeVito?
</P>
<P>
   Facinelli: I don't really get star-struck because I feel like
we're all trying to do the same thing. But I have a lot of respect
for Kevin and Danny, so I was excited. I was fully aware that they
are very powerful actors, and that I really have to try to keep up
with them.
</P>
<P>
   3. Do you and Jennie Garth ever talk about work when you're at
home?
</P>
<P>
   Facinelli: No, we don't talk about business. We talk about our
day. Acting is like any other occupation; you go home and talk
about your day. But we both do the same thing, so it's not like one
of us is trying to impress the other. But we support each other.
</P>
<P>
   4. Your daughter was born when you were 23. Was it strange to
become a father at such a young age?
</P>
<P>
   Facinelli: Yeah, definitely! When she calls me dad, sometimes I
look around the room to see who she's talking to. It's a little
weird because you don't really think of yourself as a dad, you
think of your own dad as a dad. But they don't have instruction
books for parents, so you just have to learn by experience. Having
a child helps me with my acting, too. That's what we're trying to
do, as actors, to be as free as a little kid.
</P>
<P>
   4{. How did you come up with the name Luca Bella for your
daughter? Is it a nod to your Italian heritage?
</P>
<P>
   Facinelli: I'm a first-generation American. My family came from
Italy, so it is an Italian name. My uncle's name was Luca, which
means 'light.' It's a male name, but I used it for my daughter
because I liked it, and Bella we added because it means
'beautiful,' so the full name means 'beautiful light.'
</P>
<P>
   5. What's next for Peter Facinelli?
</P>
<P>
   Facinelli: I'm going to the Caribbean islands for a few days. I
need a vacation. I haven't had one in two years.
</P>
<P>
   ------
</P>
<P>
   On the Net:
</P>
<P>
   Web site for ''The Big Kahuna'' is:
http://www.lionsgatefilms.com/thebigkahuna
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
