<HEADLINE> 4,000 Census Takers Hitting Streets  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   About 440,000 census-takers will begin visiting the
estimated 42
million households across the country that did not mail back a
census form. Here are some tips from the Department of Commerce and
the Census Bureau on how to identify census workers.
<TEXT>
<P>
   --Each census-taker must show an official, plastic census ID
card.
</P>
<P>
   --Census-takers must carry a Census 2000 tote bag filled with
questionnaire kits and a large binder filled with address lists.
</P>
<P>
   --Census-takers must show you a ''Federal Statement of Privacy''
concerning the confidentiality of information.
</P>
<P>
   --Census-takers must also provide you a form with the phone
number of the local Census Bureau office so people can call to
verify if the census-taker is legitimate.
</P>
<P>
   --Under no circumstances will a census-taker ask to enter your
home. They will only enter if you invite them.
------
</P>
<P>
   Source: Department of Commerce, Census Bureau.
</P>
</TEXT>
