<HEADLINE> Yields on 2-Year Treasury Notes Off  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- Yields on two-year Treasury notes fell in
Wednesday's auction to the lowest level in three months.
</P>
<P>
   The yield was 6.484 percent, down from 6.580 percent at the last
auction on March 29. It was the lowest rate since two-year notes
sold for 6.434 percent on Jan. 26.
</P>
<P>
   The notes will carry a coupon interest rate of 6] percent with
each $10,000 in face value selling for $9,979.80.
</P>
<P>
   A total of $12 billion in notes were sold out of bids totaling
$27.7 billion.
</P>
</TEXT>
