<HEADLINE> Man Shot, Killed As He Helps Victim  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   PALMYRA, Neb. (AP) -- A man was shot to death after stopping to
pull a woman from a burning car, investigators said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   Robert Parminter and Shannon Bluhm were found dead late Tuesday
night near the burned-out car on a rural gravel road, the Nebraska
State Patrol said.
</P>
<P>
   Police said Parminter, 45, who lived near the accident scene,
and Bluhm, 27, of Eagle, apparently did not know each other.
</P>
<P>
   A female suspect was arrested early Wednesday morning and
investigators recovered a gun believed to have been used to kill
Parminter, State Patrol spokeswoman Terri Teuber said. The suspect
was not identified.
</P>
<P>
   Investigators believe Bluhm was involved in a confrontation with
someone she knew, which may have led to the car fire. Police said
Parminter apparently saw the fire and was trying to help Bluhm when
he was killed.
</P>
