<HEADLINE> TV Morning Shows Go on the Road  </HEADLINE>
By DAVID BAUDER, AP Television Writer
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- For television's ultra-competitive morning news
shows, you can tell it's nearly May by how busy their travel agents
are.
</P>
<P>
   They're hitting the road to attract attention during the May
''sweeps'' period, when ratings are used to set local advertising
rates. It begins Thursday and lasts until May 24.
</P>
<P>
   On Thursday, ''Good Morning America'' anchors Charles Gibson and
Diane Sawyer are bicycling through northern Indiana, recording
their trip on a video diary that will be seen the next day.
</P>
<P>
   Friday's show will originate from Chicago, where Oprah Winfrey
has invited Sawyer to join her in a morning workout and breakfast.
</P>
<P>
   Matt Lauer of NBC's ''Today'' will broadcast from Vietnam on
Friday, marking the 25th anniversary of the war's end. Sen. John
McCain, a former prisoner of war, was invited by ''Today'' to give
his impressions.
</P>
<P>
   NBC paid for McCain's trip, arguing it was no different from
when it flies guests to New York City for an appearance.
</P>
<P>
   Next week ''Today'' begins its ''Where in the world is Matt
Lauer?'' promotion for the third year in a row, sending the anchor
to a mystery location each day.
</P>
<P>
   This year's gimmick: Viewers got to vote among 10 locations --
including Iceland, Niagara Falls and Prague -- to decide where Lauer
goes on May 5. More than 111,000 people voted through the ''Today''
Web site, spokeswoman Allison Gollust said.
</P>
<P>
   ''The Early Show'' on CBS sends anchor Jane Clayson to Los
Angeles next week for a three-day ''Jane Goes Country'' segment.
Clayson will be a presenter on the Academy of Country Music awards,
also being telecast by CBS next week.
</P>
<P>
   ABC is likely to have other ''Friday Breakaway'' segments as the
summer goes on, spokeswoman Sonya McNair said.
</P>
<P>
   Both ABC and NBC are launching a series of summer concerts
during the sweeps period. The ''Today'' Friday morning concerts in
Rockefeller Plaza will kick off May 5 with Steely Dan, and the
year's lineup includes 'N Sync, Diana Ross and the Supremes, Don
Henley and Britney Spears.
</P>
<P>
   ''Good Morning America'' will have a performance on May 16 with
Carly Simon in New York's Bryant Park.
</P>
<P>
   ------
</P>
<P>
   On the Net: ''Good Morning America'':
http://www.abcnews.go.com/onair/goodmorningamerica/GMAIndex.html.
</P>
<P>
   ''Today'': http://msnbc.com/news/TODAY--front.asp?ta=y.
</P>
<P>
   ''The Early Show'': http://cbs.com/earlyshow/1124bustour.shtml.
</P>
</TEXT>
