<HEADLINE> NBC Renews 'Law &AMP; Order' for 5 Years  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Fans of NBC's drama, ''Law &AMP; Order,'' won't have
to worry about whether it will be renewed for the next five years.
</P>
<P>
   NBC and Studios USA announced a deal Wednesday that will keep
the show on the air through the 2005 season. Such a long-term
renewal is unprecedented for a regular series on NBC.
</P>
<P>
   ''Law &AMP; Order'' debuted on NBC in 1990 and is enjoying its best
season in the ratings this year. It is ranked No. 13 for the season
among all prime-time shows by Nielsen Media Research.
</P>
<P>
   Its spinoff series, ''Law &AMP; Order: Special Victims Unit,'' was
renewed through 2002, the network said.
</P>
<P>
   Both shows are produced by Dick Wolf for Studios USA.
</P>
</TEXT>
