<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that moved substantially or traded
heavily Wednesday on the New York Stock Exchange and Nasdaq Stock
Market.
</P>
<P>
NYSE
</P>
<P>
Nortel Networks Corp., up 4[ to 116|
</P>
<P>
   The telecommunications equipment company's first-quarter net
loss widened, but its operating earnings jumped 80 percent, easily
topping analysts' expectations. Also, Nortel raised its revenue
forecasts for the full year.
</P>
<P>
Young &AMP; Rubicam Inc., down 2[ to 49~
</P>
<P>
   The advertising company has been exploring a possible
combination with an advertising company other than WPP Group PLC
and has had recent discussions to buy direct marketer Harte-Hanks
Inc., the Wall Street Journal reported.
</P>
<P>
Hollinger International Inc., up 2 11/16 to 12 13/16
</P>
<P>
   The company said it hopes to sell its hundreds of small
community newspapers in the U.S. and Canada and focus on improving
its big daily papers, including the Chicago Sun Times, London's
Daily Telegraph and the National Post of Canada.
</P>
<P>
Gerber Scientific Inc., down 3 15/16 to 11{
</P>
<P>
   The maker of automated manufacturing systems plans to eliminate
220 to 240 jobs, about 8 percent of its work force, by the end of
July in response to slumping sales and profits. ING Barings cut its
rating on the stock.
</P>
<P>
NASDAQ
</P>
<P>
Drkoop.com Inc., up 1\ to 3 19/32
</P>
<P>
   A day after the struggling company said it has only enough cash
to operate for another four months, investors began anticipating a
takeover. On Tuesday, Drkoop.com said it will lose about 80 cents
to 82 cents a share in the first quarter, far more than the 52-cent
loss that Wall Street analysts were expecting.
</P>
<P>
Papa John's International Inc., down 4 to 26 13/16
</P>
<P>
   The pizza company may face shrinking profit margins in the
coming quarters, analysts said. Investment firm Dain Rauscher
Wessels cut its rating on the stock to ''hold'' from ''strong
buy.''
</P>
<P>
Transaction Systems Architects, down 11 11/16 to 13 5/16
</P>
<P>
   The company, a maker of software for electronic transaction
processing, earned 5 cents per share in the most recent quarter,
down from 34 cents per share in the first quarter of 1999. The
company said it is aggressively seeking capital and partners to
help drive faster growth.
</P>
<P>
Professional Detailing Inc., up 4 3/16 to 24\
</P>
<P>
   The company earned 43 cents per share in the first quarter, up
from 25 cents in the first quarter of 1999. Professional Detailing
provides sales software for the pharmaceutical industry.
</P>
