<HEADLINE> Saints Trade Bordano to Cowboys  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW ORLEANS (AP) -- The New Orleans Saints traded linebacker
Chris Bordano to the Dallas Cowboys on Wednesday for
cornerback-kick returner Kevin Mathis.
</P>
<P>
   Mathis, 5-foot-9, 181 pounds, joined the Cowboys as an undrafted
free agent in 1997. He started four games last season.
</P>
<P>
   Bordano, 6-1 and 241 pounds, was a sixth-round draft choice by
the Saints in 1998. In 1999, he played in 15 games, starting 12,
and made 59 tackles.
</P>
<P>
   Also Wednesday, Saints Randy Mueller said his brother, Rick,
will join the team from the Jacksonville Jaguars, where he has been
director of college scouting since May 1998. Rick Mueller will
oversee player personnel and trading.
