<HEADLINE> William &AMP; Mary Coach Retires  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WILLIAMSBURG, Va. (AP) -- Charlie Woollum retired Wednesday after
six seasons as William &AMP; Mary's basketball coach.
</P>
<P>
   Woollum, 59, was 69-94 at William &AMP; Mary. He led the Tribe to a
20-7 record in 1997-98, the school's first 20-victory season in 15
years.
</P>
<P>
   ''I have been blessed to have spent 38 years in a profession
that I have loved,'' said Woollum, who coached Bucknell for 19
years before taking over the Tribe.
</P>
<P>
   The Tribe finished 11-17 last season, giving Woollum a 387-315
career mark.
</P>
