<HEADLINE> Lions Re-Sign Three Free Agents  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   PONTIAC, Mich. (AP) -- The Detroit Lions re-signed unrestricted
free-agent safeties Corwin Brown and Ryan Stewart and linebacker
Scott Kowalkowski on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   Contract terms were not disclosed.
</P>
<P>
   Brown played in 13 games for Detroit last season, his first with
the Lions and seventh in the NFL. He tied for third on the team
with 15 special teams tackles and had an interception in the Lions'
loss to Washington in the NFC wild-card playoff game.
</P>
<P>
   Kowalkowski started three games in 1999, his ninth NFL season
and sixth with Detroit, and had 36 tackles and an interception. He
also had 15 special teams tackles, giving him 85 during his six
seasons in Detroit -- more than any other Lions player during that
span.
</P>
<P>
   Stewart missed most of the 1999 season, his fourth with the
Lions, because of a groin injury that forced him onto the injured
reserve list Oct. 30. He had three tackles, including two on
special teams, and a sack.
</P>
