<HEADLINE> Young Sisters Have Pizza With Elian  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   FLORENCE, Ala. (AP) -- A trip to grandma's meant a brush with a
news headliner for 6-year-old Ashlie Fristoe and 9-year-old
Brittanie Fristoe.
</P>
<P>
   As much of the nation watched the Elian Gonzalez drama unfold,
they shared a pizza with the 6-year-old Cuban boy.
</P>
<P>
   The sisters from Muscle Shoals were staying with their
grandmother, July Zills, at an Andrews Air Force Base hotel in
Maryland on Saturday when Elian was reunited with his Cuban father
at the base -- just hours after he had been removed from the home of
his Miami relatives in the widely reported raid by federal agents.
</P>
<P>
   The girls, however, got a personal look at the focus of all the
attention, the TimesDaily newspaper in Florence reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   When the girls realized the famous guest was in their hotel,
they and their grandmother asked one of the numerous federal agents
on the base if they could meet the little boy.
</P>
<P>
   The agents asked Elian's father, Juan Miguel Gonzalez, who said
yes.
</P>
<P>
   ''I was excited,'' Brittanie told the paper.
</P>
<P>
   Brittanie, who gave Elian a stuffed animal, said Elian was nice
but quiet and they had to use an interpreter to communicate. She
also told the TimesDaily that the boy looked sad. The encounter
lasted only a few minutes.
</P>
<P>
   Juan Miguel Gonzalez gave the sisters pizza, Brittanie said. And
when they left, Elian gave Ashlie a kiss on the cheek.
</P>
<P>
   The girls' mother, Diane Fristoe, educates her daughters with
home-schooling and they had discussed Elian's plight during
lessons. Fristoe said she hopes the opportunity to meet Elian while
he's a focus of international politics provided a lesson for her
daughters.
</P>
<P>
   ''It brings television, newspaper and magazine reports on this
on a more personal level,'' she said. ''It lets them know it's
real.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
