<HEADLINE> Dead Twin Fetuses Found in WVU Dorm  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MORGANTOWN, W.Va. (AP) -- Police searched Wednesday for the
mother of twin fetuses found in a bathroom at a West Virginia
University dormitory.
</P>
<P>
   A custodian found the fetuses, believed to be about three to six
months developed, in Lyon Tower on the university's Evansdale
campus about 7:45 a.m.
</P>
<P>
   The twins could have been stillborn or aborted, said university
spokeswoman Becky Lofstead. The identity of the mother was unknown,
but she is most likely a student, Lofstead said.
</P>
<P>
   ''We're concerned about mother's health and well-being. She
might need medical treatment,'' she said.
</P>
<P>
   The fetuses were sent to the state medical examiner for an
autopsy.
</P>
