<HEADLINE> Woman dies in I-95 crash  </HEADLINE>
jcfonspr
<TEXT>
<P>
   WESTBROOK, Conn. (AP) -- A woman was killed and nine people
injured in a chain reaction crash on Interstate 95 that backed up
traffic for miles Wednesday afternoon, state police said.
</P>
<P>
   The five-vehicle accident occurred at about 2:22 p.m. between
exits 63 and 64 northbound when a Massachusetts Army Reserve truck
lost control, authorities said.
</P>
<P>
   The woman who was killed was a passenger in one of the cars,
police said. Her identity was not released Wednesday evening.
</P>
<P>
   One victim was listed in critical condition at Yale-New Haven
Hospital, a spokeswoman said. Four of the injured were in fair
condition at Lawrence and Memorial Hospital in New London, said
spokesman Kelly Anthony. Two were treated and released from the
Middlesex Hospital Shoreline clinic in Essex. The conditions of the
other victims were not available Wednesday evening.
</P>
<P>
   The northbound section of the highway was shut for several hours
before it reopened at about 6:30 p.m. Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   
</P>
</TEXT>
