<TEXT>
<P>
   CANONSBURG, Pa. (AP) -- Jaromir Jagr missed his second straight
practice Wednesday because of flulike symptoms, but should be ready
for Pittsburgh's playoff series opener against Philadelphia.
</P>
<P>
   Jagr routinely skipped practice at the end of the regular season
after developing several injuries, and the Penguins essentially let
him practice whenever he wants.
</P>
<P>
   ''I don't feel good ... a little touch of the flu,'' Jagr said.
''I just don't feel good, but it's getting better. Of course, I
want to play, but if I was a little more healthy it would be a lot
better.''
</P>
