make a run at the Flyers, who have won 16 games in a row against
the Penguins in Philadelphia. The Eastern Conference semifinal
series opens Thursday night in Philadelphia.
</P>
<P>
   ''It's too bad I couldn't practice,'' Jagr said. ''I wanted to
practice before this series, but I just couldn't do it.
</P>
<P>
   ''Sometimes, things don't go the way you want them to but,
hopefully, it's not going to affect me for long and I can get back
into the shape I want to.''
</P>
