<HEADLINE> Mutiny 4, Earthquakes 0  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   TAMPA, Fla. (AP) -- Manny Lagos scored two goals as the as the
Tampa Bay Mutiny beat the San Jose Earthquakes 4-0 on Wednesday
night in Major League Soccer.
</P>
<P>
   Raul Diaz Arce and Mamadou Diallo also scored for Tampa Bay
(4-3-0). The Mutiny are 4-0 at home, outscoring their opponents
14-3.
</P>
<P>
   Diaz Arce scored his fourth goal of the season on a penalty kick
in the eighth minute. Lagos scored on a header in the 14th-minute
and added his fourth goal on a 20-yard shot in the 58th minute.
Diallo scored in the 79th minute.
</P>
<P>
   San Jose is 2-3-1 overall and 0-3-1 on the road. The Earthquakes
have been shutout for the past 290 minutes on the road, with their
lone road goal coming on a 90th-minute penalty kick by Ronald
Cerritos in a season-opening 2-1 overtime loss at Columbus.
</P>
<P>
   A crowd of 5,510 attended the game.
</P>
