<HEADLINE> Indians 5, Mariners 3, 10 Innings  </HEADLINE>
By JIM COUR, AP Sports Writer
<TEXT>
<P>
   SEATTLE (AP) -- Einar Diaz and Jacob Cruz hit RBI singles with
two outs in the 10th inning Wednesday and the Cleveland Indians
defeated the Seattle Mariners 5-3.
</P>
<P>
   Jaret Wright, bidding to become part of the first father-son
pair to pitch no-hitters, shut down Seattle until Stan Javier's
leadoff single in the seventh inning.
</P>
<P>
   The Mariners tied it at 3 in the ninth on Jay Buhner's RBI
single off Paul Shuey (1-0). Seattle then loaded the bases with one
out, but pinch-runner Carlos Hernandez was caught in a failed
suicide squeeze attempt and David Bell struck out.
</P>
<P>
   Richie Sexson singled with one out in the Cleveland 10th off
Arthur Rhodes (1-2) and Enrique Wilson singled with two outs. Diaz
and Cruz followed with their singles.
</P>
<P>
   Wright was trying to duplicate the feat of his dad, Clyde, who
pitched a no-hitter for the California Angels against Oakland on
July 3, 1970.
</P>
<P>
   After Javier singled in the seventh, Alex Rodriguez followed by
hitting a 3-1 pitch over the center-field fence for his seventh
homer to tie it at 2.
</P>
<P>
   Manny Ramirez hit a leadoff home run in the Indians eighth for a
3-2 lead. His sixth homer came against former teammate Jose Mesa.
</P>
<P>
   Cleveland center fielder Kenny Lofton made the play of the game,
reaching over the wall to rob John Olerud of his third home run in
four days. That catch came in the fourth inning, right after
shortstop Omar Vizquel sprawled on his stomach to take away a hit
on a hard grounder by Rodriguez.
</P>
<P>
   Lofton left in the ninth because of a strained left biceps.
</P>
<P>
   It took the Indians six innings to score against rookie Rob
Ramsay. He was called up from Triple-A Tacoma to start in place of
the injured Freddy Garcia.
</P>
<P>
   Roberto Alomar bunted for a single in the sixth, stole second
and scored on a single by David Justice.
</P>
<P>
   The Indians made it 2-0 in the seventh off Mesa. Wilson doubled,
Diaz sacrificed and Lofton had a sacrifice fly.
</P>
<P>
Notes: The Indians have Thursday off before playing a three-game
weekend series against Boston at Jacobs Field. The Indians were
rained out of three games at Fenway Park last weekend. ...
Rodriguez's homer broke a 2-for-18 slump in the Mariners'
homestand. It was his first homer since hitting three in the
SkyDome on April 16.
</P>
</TEXT>
