<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tokyo Stocks Lower  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   TOKYO (AP) -- Tokyo stocks slipped early Thursday following a
retreat on Wall Street. The dollar was higher against the yen.
</P>
<P>
   The benchmark 225-issue Nikkei Stock Average shed 46.86 points,
or 0.26 percent, to 18,087.45 in the first 30 minutes of trading.
On Wednesday, the average closed down 138.02 points, or 0.8
percent.
</P>
<P>
   The dollar bought 106.22 yen, up 0.34 yen from late Wednesday in
Tokyo but below its late New York level of 106.27 yen.
</P>
<P>
   On the stock market, Tokyo players remained cautious about
prospects for the U.S. stock market. They said investors were
awaiting key U.S. economic data due out later Thursday, including
gross domestic product for the first quarter of this year.
</P>
<P>
   But traders said the Tokyo market's downside is solid amid
expectations for buying from newly established investment trusts.
</P>
<P>
   In New York, the Dow Jones industrial average fell 179.32 points
to 10,945.50 at Wednesday's close. The Nasdaq composite index
closed at 3,630.09 points, down 81.14.
</P>
<P>
   The broader Tokyo Stock Price Index of all issues listed on the
first section was down 10.42 points, or 0.62 percent, to 1,657.47.
The TOPIX closed up 2.61 points, or 0.16 percent, the day before.
</P>
<P>
   In currency dealings, traders said some foreign investors bid up
the greenback against the yen in an attempt to cover losses in U.S.
stocks by selling Japanese shares.
</P>
<P>
   But trading was moderate ahead of the release of major economic
data in the United States.
</P>
<P>
   In other currencies, the euro was traded at 98.05 yen, up from
97.60 yen late Wednesday in Tokyo.
</P>
<P>
   The yield on the benchmark 10-year Japanese government bond
stood at 1.7350 points, unchanged from Wednesday's finish. Its
price remained unchanged at 100.55.
</P>
<P>
   ------
</P>
<P>
   On the Net: Tokyo Stock Exchange: http://www.tse.or.jp./
</P>
